ion of the time needed for\neach card.","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"meX1FrSA9k"}],"key":"yMn0rYxaXV"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As the week progresses, I mark off the hours that I’ve spent on each card.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"wcNSFUHC9c"}],"key":"AG2pkFj0ej"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When the card’s hours remaining reaches 0, I move it to the “Done” list","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"ZSPU3w53YC"}],"key":"GGzinH4btZ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of the week, I click my “board cleanup” link, and it returns each card to its\noriginal project board.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"HuDj1iq7Mj"}],"key":"Uap8ne53TJ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next week, I repeat this cycle.","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"nmM0l1EztO"}],"key":"JJzM8LcAP6"}],"key":"WBhG1xZuOF"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And that’s about it - I’ve found that this process is a nice way to keep both a high-level\nview of what needs to be done for my various projects (on each project board). It also allows\nmy to dig into specific to-do items throughout the week (on my weekly board).","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"KodjdQpwxz"}],"key":"L6yydbN9Qz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":126,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’d love to hear feedback and thoughts about how other people manage their time throughout\nthe week! Hopefully some of you all find this useful.","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"ZHRQy0SlLy"}],"key":"wJ6YY094qg"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Extras","position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"key":"RKX5knz3dX"}],"identifier":"extras","label":"Extras","html_id":"extras","implicit":true,"key":"myHs3g9BPx"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":131,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Butler for Trello commands can be a little bit difficult to compose. Below I’ll post the\ntwo main commands that I use to handle all the card-moving described above.","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"key":"eVIjzQf7tz"}],"key":"oVkL7HjSkZ"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board","position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"key":"U0FDaLKOkv"}],"identifier":"the-weekly-board","label":"The weekly board","html_id":"the-weekly-board","implicit":true,"key":"pdhFnJWVuF"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":136,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board has a “butler” list where the command is defined in a card (that’s how\nyou define board-specific BFT commands). Here’s the command:","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"key":"D99fQw0ncx"}],"key":"I4TWAOY10d"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":138,"